@startuml
title Failover state machine (single-writer, async replication)

skinparam shadowing false
hide empty description

state "PRIMARY_ACTIVE\n(region-a active)" as PRIMARY_ACTIVE
state "STANDBY_READY\n(region-b standby)" as STANDBY_READY
state "PRIMARY_FAILED\n(region-a unreachable)" as PRIMARY_FAILED
state "PROMOTING\n(promote region-b)" as PROMOTING
state "NEW_PRIMARY\n(region-b active)" as NEW_PRIMARY
state "REJOINING\n(reseed + reattach)" as REJOINING

[*] --> PRIMARY_ACTIVE
PRIMARY_ACTIVE --> STANDBY_READY : streaming replication running\n(async)
STANDBY_READY --> PRIMARY_FAILED : health check fails\n(primary unreachable)
PRIMARY_FAILED --> PROMOTING : failure stable AND\nreplica healthy AND\nWAL caught up AND\nno split brain
PROMOTING --> NEW_PRIMARY : pg_ctl promote OK\n+ /admin/switch

note right of PRIMARY_ACTIVE
Single writer:
only one region should accept writes.
end note

note right of STANDBY_READY
Replica visibility is eventual:
async WAL streaming.
end note

note right of NEW_PRIMARY
After promotion, replication stops.
Regions may diverge.
end note

NEW_PRIMARY --> REJOINING : manual failback procedure\n(reset volumes in this lab)
REJOINING --> PRIMARY_ACTIVE : region-a reseeded\nregion-b back to standby

@enduml

